his prose has been translated. This translation will enable students with limited or no knowledge of Chinese to get a full sense of Wang Wei's compositional range. Moreover, since Wang Wei was known for being a devout Buddhist, having the complete poetry available in reliable translation as well as all of the prose that is connected to the Buddhist faith will be useful to students of Chinese religion.  afunded by The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh  aChinese Poetry.  a Asian Literature.  a Asian Studies.  a Buddhism.1 aNugent, Christopher, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt2 aThe Andrew W. Mellon Foundationefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97815015075950 cpr